y duration-300" href="/diversity">Diversity &amp; Inclusion</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/sustainability">Sustainability</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/contact">Contact</a></div></nav><button class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e ml-10 toggle-menu absolute top-6 right-6"><img src="/images/misc/menu-closed.svg" alt="Open Menu" class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e"/></button></header><div class="bg-white"><main class="bg-white" style="opacity:0"><article class="px-2 md:px-6 py-10 md:py-12"><header class="flex px-2 md:px-0 md:pb-12 border-b flex-wrap items-center"><div class="md:w-6/12"><picture><img height="1504" width="2700" class="" loading="lazy" src="https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Screenshot_2024_01_22_at_15_29_28_5f75680a1d.png" alt=""/><sub class="mt-2"></sub></picture></div><div class="md:w-6/12 px-0 md:px-12 py-4 md:py-16 mx-auto max-w-titles small-body"><div class="font-small uppercase mb-4">Jan 22, 2024</div><h2>In The Spotlight: Pony Sun</h2><div class="max-w-sm"><div class="rich-text">Condé Nast China’s Deputy Talent Management Director Pony Sun discusses Lunar New Year, working on tentpole events and hosting “The Daily Talk.”</div></div><div class="mt-4 md:mt-8 small-body flex flex-wrap"></div></div></header><div class="small-body text-black px-2 md:px-0 py-8 md:py-36 mx-auto news-article-body"><div class="rich-text"><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Tell us a little bit about yourself. How did you find your way to Condé Nast?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I hold a master's degree in International Journalism and have been working in the fashion media industry for nearly two decades. I had always aspired to join Condé Nast and only did so after establishing myself as a proficient professional in the field. It's been five years since I became a member of Condé Nast.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>How do you describe your job to friends and family?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">My job is all about making your life more beautiful, stylish and merrier.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Lunar New Year is approaching soon, what does this holiday mean to you and how do you plan to celebrate?</strong>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Due to my usual hectic schedule and frequent business travels to various cities for shoots, I plan to truly enjoy quality time with my family during this holiday break.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Reflecting on 2023, what is a project that you worked on that you are most proud of?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Among the dozens of projects I participated in, the most impressive one was the collaboration between Condé Nast and Tommy Hilfiger. This project covered the Asia Pacific region, and the Chinese, Japanese and Korean versions of Vogue to participate in filming.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">This was a big collaboration across countries and departments.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">After six months of cooperation, I overcame the time difference, worked with colleagues late into the night, established a deep friendship and successfully completed this project.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>In August of 2023, Condé Nast China received the High-Energy Innovation Team Award for its initiative ‘Three Senses.’ Tell us about what the initiative is and how it started.&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Our managing director Gill Zhou wanted to foster a more cohesive sense of belonging among colleagues in various innovative ways. I chose to contribute based on my own strengths to volunteer as the host of “Daily Talk,” a cultural transformation program in the form of broadcast on the wecom platform to inform Chinese employees about what is happening within the company everyday. Some of the topics included holiday greetings, company activities information, leadership announcements — a true information hub glueing different functions together.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>You are the host of the popular internal program, ‘The Daily Talk’ within Condé Nast China. Can you tell us more about it?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">“Daily Talk” is currently one of the most popular cultural-transformation projects from the “Three Senses” taskforce with Condé Nast China. It has received the Cultural Wave-Making Award twice.</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">With a daily episode format, the process involves writing scripts, recording, editing and&nbsp; broadcasting. Despite the substantial workload, I feel extremely warmed up and encouraged inside. Through the program, I aim to foster a sense of belonging among all colleagues through the heartful content. The recording often begins after work and yet the thought that each colleague looks forward to listening to the program the next day always inspires me to commit to the program.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>What are the successful marketing campaigns that Condé Nast China has implemented in the past year that you are particularly proud of?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Vogue Forces of Fashion and GQ Men of the Year (MOTY)!</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>What was your role in the campaign and what did you learn or gain from it?</strong>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I’m responsible for managing talent to participate in our marketing events and activities across titles, owning the full cycle of entertainer collaboration. I manage the invitations, coordination of all details, and aligning/execution of all business terms with the talent and their agents. Throughout all working processes, I consistently prioritize maximizing profits for the company and strive to reduce costs, dedicating to securing greater profitability and cost-effectiveness for Condé Nast China.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>What is something that you are currently working on that you are most excited about?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Working with colleagues from different departments every day to generate more revenue for the company.</span></p></div></div></article></main></div><div><footer id="footer" class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e px-4 py-4 md:px-6 md:py-6 block bg-near-black"><section class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e border-b border-dark-border pt-12 mb-8 overflow-x-auto"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e snap-mandatory snap-x flex overflow-nav-group"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/about">About</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/brands">Brands</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/advertising">Advertising</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/entertainment">Entertainment</a></div><div class=